text:
When there is no court order but custody applies, determine if one parent has a higher responsibility, or it is shared equally (50/50).
One Parent Has Higher Responsibility
When one parent has higher responsibility, the order of coverage is as follows.
1.	Natural parent with custody.
2.	Stepparent with custody.
3.	Natural parent without custody.
4.	Stepparent without custody.
Parents Have Equal Responsibility
When the parents have 50/50 responsibility, the order of coverage is as follows.
1.	Natural parent who is primary according to the birthday rule.
2.	Spouse of primary parent.
3.	Natural parent who is secondary according to the birthday rule.
4.	Spouse of secondary parent.
